t`, and `CapturedLaunchResult` inside the original test file to exercise public contracts without external services.\\n- **Add separate replacement feature test**: Added `QuarkusJunitCallbackContextTest.java` instead of changing existing tests after the previous feature test did not pass.\\n- **Cover callback context API**: Selected Quarkus JUnit callback interfaces and context objects as a different lightweight feature likely to execute under Native Image.\\n- **Do not exclude `jboss-logmanager` from JVM runtime**: Excluding it caused `NoClassDefFoundError: org/jboss/logmanager/handlers/AsyncHandler$OverflowAction` before tests could start.\\n- **Use native-image class initialization args**: Native compilation fails due to JBoss logging and SmallRye reference objects in the image heap, so `build.gradle` was updated with build-time initialization arguments.\\n- **Exclude Quarkus JUnit service-loaded test listeners/callback from Native Image discovery**: Added `-H:ServiceLoaderFeatureExcludeServiceProviders` for Quarkus JUnit launcher/listener providers to reduce build-time initialization of problematic logging paths.\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n1. Re-run the external command `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.quarkus:quarkus-junit:3.33.1`.\\n2. If JVM `:test` fails again, inspect `tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-junit/3.33.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-Gradle#20Test#20Executor#201.xml` and restore any missing runtime dependencies.\\n3. If Native Image still fails, inspect the new image-heap error and adjust only necessary `build.gradle` native args or simplify tests/imports to avoid triggering problematic classes.\\n4. Preserve Native Image execution and do not introduce skips, assumptions, or native-runtime guards.\\n5. Ensure `Quarkus_junitTest.java` remains unchanged unless explicitly required.\\n\\n## Critical Context\\n- Main test file path:\\n  `tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-junit/3.33.1/src/test/java/io_quarkus/quarkus_junit/Quarkus_junitTest.java`\\n- Replacement featur